'''Jean-Baptiste Rondelet''' (4 June 1743 &ndash; 25 September 1829) was an architectural theorist of the late [[Enlightenment era]] and chief architect of the [[Panthéon (Paris)|church of Sainte-Geneviève]] after the death of [[Jacques Germain Soufflot]] of cancer in 1780. 

Rondelet published a treatise on [[architecture]] between 1805 and 1816.

